-- RBS Said to Plan Sale of Covered Bonds in Pounds Due 2024
-- B y   H a n n a h   B e n j a m i n
-- 2012-01-10T09:11:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-10/rbs-said-to-plan-sale-of-covered-bonds-in-pounds-due-2024.html
Royal Bank of Scotland Group Plc (RBS) 
plans to sell covered bonds in pounds due 2024, according to a
banker involved in the deal.  The notes may be priced to yield 275 basis points more than
gilts. BNP Paribas SA, JPMorgan Chase & Co., Lloyds Banking
Group Plc and  RBC Capital Markets  are managing the transaction
with RBS.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Hannah Benjamin in London at 
 hbenjamin1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
